course_description: Pre-Requisites: BIOS 516D and AEPI 530D as prerequisites or by special permission to enroll. This course is an introduction to the SAS programming environment. This is an applied computer course that instructs students in the techniques needed to enter data into a database and properly read and process data into a final dataset that is ready for epidemiologic analysis.
prerequisites: BIOS 516D and AEPI 530D as prerequisites or special permission required to enroll.
